---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import Navbar from "../components/Navbar.astro";
import Footer from "../components/Footer.astro";

const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;
const updated = "12 July 2026";
const contactEmail = "pratiksingh30701@gmail.com";

const h2 = "text-xl md:text-2xl font-[family-name:var(--font-display)] font-semibold text-[var(--color-ink)] mt-10 mb-3";
const p = "text-[var(--color-ink-dim)] leading-relaxed mb-4";
const ul = "list-disc pl-6 text-[var(--color-ink-dim)] leading-relaxed mb-4 space-y-1.5";
const link = "text-[var(--color-coral)] underline hover:text-[var(--color-coral-hover)] transition-colors";
---

<Layout
  title="Privacy Policy — Minnie"
  description="How Minnie handles the information you share when you join the waitlist. Privacy-first: minimal data, no tracking cookies, and you stay in control."
>
  <Navbar />

  <main class="mx-auto w-full max-w-3xl px-6 md:px-10 py-16 md:py-24">
    <a href={base} class={`${link} text-sm no-underline hover:underline`}>← Back to home</a>

    <h1 class="font-[family-name:var(--font-display)] text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold tracking-tight text-[var(--color-ink)] mt-6">
      Privacy Policy
    </h1>
    <p class="text-sm text-[var(--color-lilac-muted)] mt-3">Last updated: {updated}</p>

    <p class={`${p} mt-8`}>
      Minnie ("we", "us") builds a native macOS desktop pet that runs your AI coding
      agent locally. This policy explains what information this website collects when
      you join the waitlist, how we use it, and the choices you have. Privacy is core
      to the product, and it applies to this site too: we collect the minimum needed
      and never sell your data.
    </p>

    <h2 class={h2}>What we collect</h2>
    <p class={p}>When you submit the waitlist form, we collect only:</p>
    <ul class={ul}>
      <li>Your <strong>email address</strong>.</li>
      <li>The <strong>form source</strong> (which section you signed up from, e.g. hero or final CTA) — so we understand what resonates.</li>
      <li>The <strong>submission timestamp</strong>, added automatically when your entry is recorded.</li>
    </ul>
    <p class={p}>
      We do not ask for your name, and we do not use tracking cookies, fingerprinting,
      or advertising pixels. We do not collect anything from you unless you choose to
      submit the form.
    </p>

    <h2 class={h2}>How your information is stored</h2>
    <p class={p}>
      Waitlist entries are sent to a private Google Sheet via Google Apps Script and
      stored there. Google LLC processes and stores this data on our behalf as an
      infrastructure provider; their handling is governed by
      <a class={link} href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Google's Privacy Policy</a>.
    </p>

    <h2 class={h2}>How we use your information</h2>
    <ul class={ul}>
      <li>To notify you when Minnie launches and when early access opens.</li>
      <li>To honor founder pricing for people on the waitlist.</li>
      <li>To send occasional, relevant product updates about Minnie.</li>
    </ul>
    <p class={p}>We will not use your email for unrelated marketing, and we will not add you to lists you didn't sign up for.</p>

    <h2 class={h2}>Analytics</h2>
    <p class={p}>
      We use <a class={link} href="https://www.cloudflare.com/web-analytics/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Cloudflare Web Analytics</a>,
      a privacy-first, cookieless analytics tool. It reports aggregate traffic (like
      page views and referrers) without cookies, without cross-site tracking, and
      without building a profile of you. It does not identify individual visitors.
    </p>

    <h2 class={h2}>Sharing &amp; disclosure</h2>
    <p class={p}>
      We do not sell or rent your information. We share it only with the service
      providers that operate this site and store our data — currently Google (waitlist
      storage), GitHub (hosting), and Cloudflare (analytics) — and only to the extent
      needed to provide the service. We may disclose information if required by law.
    </p>

    <h2 class={h2}>Data retention</h2>
    <p class={p}>
      We keep waitlist entries until Minnie has launched and for a reasonable period
      afterward, or until you ask us to remove you — whichever comes first. Ask any
      time and we'll delete your entry.
    </p>

    <h2 class={h2}>Your rights &amp; choices</h2>
    <p class={p}>
      You can ask us to access, correct, or delete the information we hold about you,
      and you can unsubscribe from updates at any time. To make a request, email
      <a class={link} href={`mailto:${contactEmail}`}>{contactEmail}</a>. Depending on
      where you live (for example, the EEA/UK under GDPR, or California under the CCPA),
      you may have additional rights; we honor these requests regardless of location.
    </p>

    <h2 class={h2}>Children's privacy</h2>
    <p class={p}>
      This site is intended for developers and is not directed at children under 16.
      We do not knowingly collect information from children.
    </p>

    <h2 class={h2}>Changes to this policy</h2>
    <p class={p}>
      We may update this policy as the product evolves. Material changes will be posted
      here with a new "last updated" date.
    </p>

    <h2 class={h2}>Contact</h2>
    <p class={p}>
      Questions about this policy or your data? Email
      <a class={link} href={`mailto:${contactEmail}`}>{contactEmail}</a>.
    </p>
  </main>

  <Footer />
</Layout>
